    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "## Problem\n\n`vim.filetype.add` allows one to register custom filetypes, and `filetype.lua` defines ~700 filetypes. These tables are module-local with no public accessor. \"What filetypes does Neovim know how to detect?\" is an unanswerable question rn.\n\n`vim.fn.getcompletion('', 'filetype')` (related: #38082) is sometimes used as a proxy for\nthis but it only scans `syntax/`, `indent/`, and `ftplugin/` directories on the `runtimepath`. (i.e. not the neovim/lua filetype registry_. So, 125+ built-in filetypes in `filetype.lua` are expectedly undetected by `getcompletion`.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nA public API (e.g. `vim.filetype.get()`) that returns all filetype strings including `vim.filetype.add`.\n\nNote: values in these tables can be functions (detection callbacks), not\n\nHappy to open a PR for this.",
    "closed_at": "2026-02-27T16:58:26Z",
