            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hmm, I see. Personally, I think this is a bit too \"Clippy\" (\"I see you typed `makdown` -- did you mean `markdown`?) to include as a default health check, but I can see the value of such a check.\n\nSo, yes, I don't think this proposal is a reasonable approach to the linked issue (or even reasonable to solve, see below), so I'd rather suggest rethinking the health check itself.\n\n---\nimagine something like\n```lua\nvim.filetype.add({\n  pattern = {\n    ['*'] = function(path, bufnr)\n      if path:match('mydev') then\n        return path .. '.mydev'\n      else\n        return vim.uv.hrtime()\n      end\n    end\n  }})\n```\n\n(obviously facetious, especially the `else` branch, but \"dynamic\" filetypes are definitely a possibility, e.g., for template languages).\n\n",
