            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Is there currently any way for users to inspect the structures maintained by vim.filetype.add() ?\n\nNo, because the tables (`extension`, `filename`, and `pattern`) are (intentionally) private. But a low-level `vim.filetype.inspect()` that simply returns these (so people can see what is registered at all, even if not the result (since that is dynamic)) would be easily possible and fit with the general policy.\n\nOutput would be something like\n\n<img width=\"474\" height=\"438\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8e56a981-17f8-426e-b69e-b125719da31a\" />",
            "created_at": "2026-04-06T13:59:35Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38081#issuecomment-4192644723",
            "id": 4192644723,
